course.subject: STSCI
course.course_title: Bayesian Data Analysis: Principles and Practice

notes.note: Prerequisites: Basic multivariate differential and integral calculus (e.g., MATH 1120 or 2220), basic linear algebra (e.g., MATH 2210, 2310 or 2940), familiarity with some programming language or numerical computing environment (like R, Python, MATLAB, Octave, IDL).
Problem solving sessions to prepare students for the first four actuarial examinations (probability, financial mathematics, statistical modeling, and risk management).

Prerequisites: Knowledge of a general purpose computer programming language, such as JAVA, Python, Ruby, or C++, or at least taking STSC 4060 in parallel with this course; STSCI 5060 or basic SQL knowledge; STSCI 5010 or basic knowledge of SAS programming; STSCI 3520 or STSCI 4030 or basic knowledge of R programming.
